article.description: Daniel Smith ran for two touchdowns and passed for two more as Campbell blanked Division II Shaw, 42-0 in a nonconference game Saturday.
article.headline: Smith's 4 TDs power Campbell past Division II Shaw, 42-0
article.linkText: Smith's 4 TDs power Campbell past Division II Shaw, 42-0
article.story: BLUIES CREEK, N.C. -- Daniel Smith ran for two touchdowns and passed for two more as Campbell blanked Division II Shaw, 42-0 in a nonconference game Saturday. Smith opened the scoring barely a minute into the game, dashing 59 yards on the third play from scrimmage for a touchdown. He punched in from the 1 before halftime to give the Camels a 35-0 lead. Smith completed 22 of 28 passes for 227 yards and added five carries for 100 yards. Rocky Reid ran for two touchdowns in the first quarter. Aaron Blockmon caught a 25-yard touchdown pass from Smith early in the second quarter and Antonio Wheeler pulled in a 22-yard pass for a score in the third. Campbell (3-1) held Shaw (1-2) to 174 yards of total offense and forced the Bears to punt nine times.
